  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nIn spite of what the [docs](https://buidler.dev/guides/buidler-console.html#using-the-buidler-console) say, the \"ethers\" and \"waffle\" objects are not available in the global scope when I do:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nyarn buidler console\r\n```\r\n\r\nI suspect that this is caused by TypeScript, but I'm not sure how exactly. I created a repository that reproduces the issue:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/paulrberg/buidler-console-bug\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n+ @nomiclabs/buidler@1.3.3\r\n+ @nomiclabs-ethers/buidler@1.3.3\r\n+ @nomiclabs-waffle/buidler@1.3.3\r\n+ node@12.16.3\r\n+ macOS@10.15.4\r\n",
